# Reference only -- NOT loaded automatically by anything. Every
# REPLACE_ME_* placeholder repeated across the per-service files in this
# directory means the same thing every time it appears:
#
#   REPLACE_ME_DB_HOST        host of the staging Postgres instance
#   REPLACE_ME_DB_PASSWORD    the `platform` role's real password (not "platform")
#   REPLACE_ME_KAFKA_BROKERS  e.g. "kafka-1.staging.internal:9092,kafka-2.staging.internal:9092"
#   REPLACE_ME_REDIS_HOST     e.g. "redis.staging.internal:6379"
#   REPLACE_ME_CLICKHOUSE_URL e.g. "https://clickhouse.staging.internal:8123"
#   REPLACE_ME_JWT_SECRET     a real random secret -- must be IDENTICAL in
#                             auth-service.env.example and
#                             api-gateway.env.example (auth-service signs
#                             tokens, api-gateway verifies them)
#   REPLACE_ME_DOMAIN         the staging domain this platform is deployed under
#
# Internal service-to-service URLs below use the placeholder scheme
# "http://<service>.staging.internal:<port>" -- replace with whatever real
# internal DNS/service-discovery scheme staging actually uses (K8s Service
# DNS, a service mesh, etc.) once that infrastructure exists.
